        <updateDate>2012-07-10T20:55:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Early Treatment for HIV Act of 2012 - Amends title XIX (Medicaid) of the Social Security Act (SSA) to: (1) give states the option to provide Medicaid coverage for low-income HIV-infected individuals, and (2) provide an enhanced federal medical assistance percentage (FMAP) to states taking this option.</p> <p>Amends SSA title XI to exempt medical assistance for optional low-income HIV-infected individuals from the funding limitation for territories.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
